			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				I have played on Veeshan for a while and need some infos on PvP: <br>  <br> 1. Can I start different characters on different servers? <br> 2. Which PvP Servers are there? <br> 3. I heard about Coin loot and else - what is the difference, how much stuff can u take if u kill your opponent? <br> 4. Do u loose exp everytime you are pk`d? <br> 5. I read in another post that a lvl 2 can be killed by a lvl 10. Is this true? This seems highly unfair to me. <br> 6. Is there any way to advance without friends? I play at european hours and have not much time for playing. <br> 7. How does pvp work: U log on, kill the first one in sight, loot, go to the bank, go back and kill more or people do still go for muds and quests? <br> 8. Are towns safe from pk? <br>  <br> OK, thats enough for one post. Tx for replying <br>  <br> Mascha		

